Diamons Price Estimation with CaRT

In this article iâll try to predict prices of diamonds using decision trees. diamonds Dataset is used in tidyverse package.
CART modeling method is used for predicting prices.

Diamond dataset is containing the prices and other attributes of diamonds such as carat, clarity etc.

Dataset contains 53940 obversations and 10 variables.

Structure of Dataset

## Observations: 53,940
## Variables: 10
## $ carat   <dbl> 0.23, 0.21, 0.23, 0.29, 0.31, 0.24, 0.24, 0.26, 0.22, ...
## $ cut     <ord> Ideal, Premium, Good, Premium, Good, Very Good, Very G...
## $ color   <ord> E, E, E, I, J, J, I, H, E, H, J, J, F, J, E, E, I, J, ...
## $ clarity <ord> SI2, SI1, VS1, VS2, SI2, VVS2, VVS1, SI1, VS2, VS1, SI...
## $ depth   <dbl> 61.5, 59.8, 56.9, 62.4, 63.3, 62.8, 62.3, 61.9, 65.1, ...
## $ table   <dbl> 55, 61, 65, 58, 58, 57, 57, 55, 61, 61, 55, 56, 61, 54...
## $ price   <int> 326, 326, 327, 334, 335, 336, 336, 337, 337, 338, 339,...
## $ x       <dbl> 3.95, 3.89, 4.05, 4.20, 4.34, 3.94, 3.95, 4.07, 3.87, ...
## $ y       <dbl> 3.98, 3.84, 4.07, 4.23, 4.35, 3.96, 3.98, 4.11, 3.78, ...
## $ z       <dbl> 2.43, 2.31, 2.31, 2.63, 2.75, 2.48, 2.47, 2.53, 2.49, ...

Description of each variables

Variables Description
carat weight of the diamond (0.2â5.01)
cut quality of the cut (Fair, Good, Very Good, Premium, Ideal)
color diamond colour, from J (worst) to D (best)
clarity a measurement of how clear the diamond is (I1 (worst), SI2, SI1, VS2, VS1, VVS2, VVS1, IF (best))
depth total depth percentage = z / mean(x, y) = 2 * z / (x + y) (43â79)
table width of top of diamond relative to widest point (43â95)
price price in US dollars ($326â$18,823)
x length in mm (0â10.74)
y width in mm (0â58.9)
z depth in mm (0â31.8)

Exploring the data

Correlation of variable with Price

If we examine the correlation of variables with price. We can see that there is strong positive correlation with x,y,z and carat. Correlation with table and depth variable is low.

##   cor_x_price cor_y_price cor_z_price cor_depth_price cor_table_price2
## 1   0.8844352   0.8654209   0.8612494      -0.0106474        0.1271339
##   cor_carat_price3
## 1        0.9215913

As the carat of diamond increases price also increase as stated in correlation also. Event carat is same price range is very big. This shows us that there are other variables that effect the price also.

Letâs add the clarity informatio to plot.

CART modelling

First we prepare the dataset we use to train the model then test the model.

As there is no correlation between price and table&depth. These variables are removed. We use the Complexity parameter as 0.001.
